Dialogue: 0,0:00:00.73,0:00:04.05,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Encounters are mysterious!\NBut cases are even more so!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:04.05,0:00:06.25,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}I'm so glad I'm with you!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:06.25,0:00:10.15,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Today's stage is a clock manor!\NThe case's alarms all ring together!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:10.15,0:00:11.72,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}He sees the single truth for what it is,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:11.72,0:00:13.72,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}and looks like a kid but has the mind of an adult.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:13.72,0:00:16.22,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}His name? Detective Conan!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:46.88,0:01:52.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"Dear Kogoro Mouri.\NI'm sorry for the sudden letter.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:52.79,0:01:56.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Getting directly to the point,\NI would like you, the great detective,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:56.79,0:02:02.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,to solve the mysteries concerning strange events in my home.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:02.13,0:02:07.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's actually an old mansion given to me by my grandfather,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:07.07,0:02:10.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,who passed away very recently.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:10.14,0:02:14.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Since moving in, strange events have been occurring daily,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:14.38,0:02:19.28,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,and I've even had the feeling that I'm being watched lately.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:19.28,0:02:24.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I tried to figure it out on my own, as I'm a simple mystery writer,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:24.02,0:02:28.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,but seeing as I haven't been here long\Nand don't know the house well,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:28.26,0:02:31.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I figured I wouldn't discover anything on my own,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:31.50,0:02:34.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,which is why I've sent you this letter."
Dialogue: 0,0:02:38.47,0:02:45.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"On his deathbed, my grandfather said the mansion was special,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:45.04,0:02:48.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,which I find very strange now.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:48.05,0:02:52.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If you're interested, please come before 10:30 AM.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:52.78,0:02:56.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I look forward to hearing from you. Misao Nakamura."
Dialogue: 0,0:02:57.69,0:03:00.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm coming, Misao{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-chan{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:01.73,0:03:06.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I've deduced that she's a lonely, talented woman in her late 20s!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:06.06,0:03:11.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Are you sure? It sounded like some glum guy in his early 30s to me.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:11.87,0:03:18.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,How dumb! Why would I rent a car and go there on a Sunday then?!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:18.68,0:03:24.28,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Couldn't you have told if it was a man or a woman on the phone?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:24.28,0:03:31.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I didn't call. I'm gonna show up and make an exciting entrance!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:32.59,0:03:35.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What do you want to excite this person for?!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:35.36,0:03:38.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He's such a lost cause...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:38.80,0:03:43.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What do you think, Conan{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}?\NIs it a man or a woman?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:43.17,0:03:46.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I don't know. The handwriting {\i1}is{\i0} nice...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:48.57,0:03:51.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Maybe it {\i1}is{\i0} a woman?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:56.81,0:04:00.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Dad! That's dangerous!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:02.45,0:04:08.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,S-Sorry! I messed up!\NI haven't done this in a while!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:08.49,0:04:10.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Forgive me, Misao{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-chan{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:10.66,0:04:12.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No one can forgive this!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:20.07,0:04:22.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I think I'll take the train back.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:22.24,0:04:28.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What're you talking about?\NThat was a pleasant family drive!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:28.25,0:04:30.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You call that pleasant?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:30.08,0:04:35.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Just look at this refreshing sunlight coming through the leaves!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:35.69,0:04:38.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Doesn't it just relieve your mind?!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:38.46,0:04:42.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah. I'm relieved we actually made it to our destination.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:47.03,0:04:54.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Whadya think? This large mansion is surrounded by trees and nature!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:54.04,0:04:58.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But..."It's so lonely for a single woman!"
Dialogue: 0,0:05:00.38,0:05:06.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"Misao{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}! At long last, your Kogoro Mouri has arrived!"
Dialogue: 0,0:05:06.05,0:05:10.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I've recently started to understand why Mom left you...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:10.72,0:05:12.05,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Yeah...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:22.73,0:05:24.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:26.07,0:05:30.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, Mouri{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}! You came!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:30.54,0:05:34.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Here, we can say hello inside!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:34.08,0:05:36.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Y-Yeah...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:37.18,0:05:39.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,See! I told you!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:39.45,0:05:43.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Say. Did {\i1}you{\i0} send this letter?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:43.32,0:05:47.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No, the person who wrote that letter is my three-years-younger...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:47.56,0:05:50.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Your younger sister?!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:50.23,0:05:52.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,My younger brother, Misao.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:52.43,0:05:55.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hi, there!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:55.13,0:05:57.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:57.33,0:05:59.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm the one who inherited this mansion,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:59.90,0:06:03.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,but it's so big that I moved in with my brother.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:03.91,0:06:06.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What happened to your arm?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:06.88,0:06:09.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I hurt it while moving some shelves.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:09.35,0:06:13.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's bad. Especially for a writer.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:13.15,0:06:18.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's only a sprain. The doctor just went overboard and wrapped it up.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:18.39,0:06:21.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Anyways, come inside!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:25.20,0:06:26.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What is it, Conan{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:26.93,0:06:29.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Doesn't this seem strange?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:29.53,0:06:35.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There's a tiger on that pillar, but not on this one.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:35.51,0:06:38.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It has weird holes instead...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:38.74,0:06:41.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Maybe they planned to put something there, but decided not to?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:41.88,0:06:43.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:43.68,0:06:45.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Come in already.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:45.69,0:06:46.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:46.92,0:06:48.34,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Let's go, Conan{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:48.34,0:06:49.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Okay!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:56.89,0:06:59.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Wow! How cute!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:59.86,0:07:03.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What an amazing collection!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:03.13,0:07:07.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There are animals on almost all the furniture and dishes!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:07.04,0:07:09.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh! Is this a seal?!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:09.94,0:07:15.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ran{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-neechan{\r}. That's a walrus.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:15.15,0:07:16.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Really?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:17.71,0:07:21.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,All this junk everywhere makes the place stuffy...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:21.35,0:07:26.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Surprised? Our late grandfather absolutely loved animals!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:26.79,0:07:31.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He always used to say that animals that hunted to live
Dialogue: 0,0:07:31.26,0:07:38.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,were much better than humans who fool others out of sheer greed.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:38.60,0:07:44.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Animals aside, there sure are a lot of clocks here...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:44.68,0:07:49.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But of course. Our grandfather was a clockmaker!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:49.35,0:07:51.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A clockmaker?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:51.11,0:07:54.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes. His name was Monjiro Izubuchi.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:54.02,0:07:56.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He made quite a name for himself;
Dialogue: 0,0:07:56.79,0:08:02.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"Monjiro's clocks last a lifetime,"\Npeople came to say!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:03.46,0:08:06.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then this digital bunny clock was his, too?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:06.33,0:08:10.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No, our grandfather only made screw-operated clocks.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:10.50,0:08:13.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He probably just collected those ones for fun.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:13.30,0:08:17.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I see. There's a crack on this digital clock.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:17.57,0:08:22.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He must've handled things he didn't make without much care.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:22.35,0:08:24.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,See? This one, too. And this one.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:24.88,0:08:29.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's strange. He always took great care of his things...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:29.72,0:08:33.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Doesn't this clock seem strange too?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:33.16,0:08:36.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It looks like something used to be attached to it...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:36.19,0:08:40.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It probably came off when he dropped it or something.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:40.43,0:08:42.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:44.20,0:08:46.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Is this a photo of Monjiro{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:46.87,0:08:50.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes! It's from quite a long time ago, though.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:50.01,0:08:53.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Who's the girl with him?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:53.68,0:08:57.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, that's his friend's granddaughter.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:57.01,0:09:02.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He always used to take me and my brother to the golf course.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:02.22,0:09:06.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then this golf bag was Monjiro{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:06.86,0:09:08.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"Demon"?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:08.29,0:09:17.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You know, it's what they call people who score over 100 in golf.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:17.40,0:09:19.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Our grandfather could never improve his score,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:19.40,0:09:21.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,so we gave him that as a joke present.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:21.87,0:09:27.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Say, wasn't "Demons" the name of an old bandit gang?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:27.74,0:09:33.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You know, the gang that only stole from bad companies and people!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:33.38,0:09:39.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Don't be dumb. Those were the Goblins, not the Demons.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:42.06,0:09:44.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm sorry! I should've been helping!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:48.20,0:09:50.20,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Here it is again!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:50.20,0:09:55.31,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}All the other cups have animals on their handles, but not this one.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:55.31,0:09:59.94,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}And it's been carefully filed down afterwards.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:59.94,0:10:04.31,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}If the animal had fallen off, it could've been easily glued back on.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:04.31,0:10:06.02,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}So why?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:06.02,0:10:08.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Conan{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:08.09,0:10:09.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Thanks.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:09.72,0:10:11.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'll clean this up!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:11.82,0:10:13.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, thanks...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:13.69,0:10:20.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So, could you tell me about these strange happenings you spoke of?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:20.03,0:10:22.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, you mean the clock.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:22.90,0:10:25.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Clock?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:25.04,0:10:28.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,10:48... Perfect timing...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:28.37,0:10:31.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Come to the study. I'll let you see for yourself.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:36.75,0:10:39.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Damn. It's stuck again.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:39.32,0:10:43.34,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, have you forgotten? You gotta kick the bottom right part.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:46.59,0:10:47.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,See?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:47.48,0:10:49.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, right.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:49.40,0:10:55.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You leave the curtains shut,\Neven though it's so stifling in here?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:55.17,0:11:00.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's like I mentioned in the letter.\NIt feels like someone's watching us.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:00.44,0:11:02.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So that's why.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:08.11,0:11:10.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There's a hole over here.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:10.95,0:11:16.21,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, really? Well, this house {\i1}is{\i0} old and falling apart.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:17.22,0:11:21.02,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Only a tool could've made such a clean hole!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:21.02,0:11:23.56,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}What in the world is it for?!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:23.56,0:11:26.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So, about this clock...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:26.36,0:11:30.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, right. Let's see... It's a cuckoo-clock...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:30.97,0:11:33.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:33.44,0:11:36.27,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Isn't this it?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:36.27,0:11:38.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, yes! That's it!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:38.91,0:11:40.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Geez...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:40.84,0:11:45.28,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Looks like an ordinary cuckoo clock to me.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:45.28,0:11:47.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Is there something to it?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:47.15,0:11:49.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It rings at a certain time.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:49.52,0:11:53.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Of course it does. It's a cuckoo clock.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:53.32,0:11:56.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No, it happens at a weird time.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:56.53,0:11:58.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Every 10:50 or so.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:58.86,0:12:04.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And something strange comes out of it instead of a cuckoo.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:04.73,0:12:06.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Something strange?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:06.57,0:12:08.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Just watch!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:08.61,0:12:10.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Should be any time now!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:17.88,0:12:20.42,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Nothing's happening.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:20.42,0:12:25.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,T-That's odd! It came out last time!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:25.52,0:12:28.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Are you sure it isn't just broken?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:28.49,0:12:30.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Of course it isn't!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:30.09,0:12:33.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Our grandfather's clocks are known for never breaking!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:33.53,0:12:37.27,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This is ridiculous. I'm going home.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:37.27,0:12:41.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,W-Wait, Mouri{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}! There's another strange thing that needs solving!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:41.51,0:12:43.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Please!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:45.38,0:12:47.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The VCR's timer has been set, too...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:47.71,0:12:52.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Let go! I told you, I'm leaving!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:06.66,0:13:09.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,W-What is this?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:11.54,0:13:15.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's crazy, Dad! All the clocks in the house are ringing!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:15.41,0:13:18.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,T-The entire house?!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:18.07,0:13:21.08,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Even the VCR is running!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:21.08,0:13:24.54,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}What in the world is going on here?!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:33.12,0:13:36.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,All the clocks in the house are ringing?!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:36.29,0:13:39.39,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}What in the world is going on here?!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:43.94,0:13:46.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I-It stopped!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:46.44,0:13:49.17,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}The video ran for only a minute, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:50.37,0:13:52.21,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}But why?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:11.50,0:14:12.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What was that?!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:12.87,0:14:14.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A cat.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:14.43,0:14:18.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A big cat's taken up lodging in the attic and we can't get rid of it.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:18.74,0:14:21.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Anyway, think you can solve the mystery of the clocks
Dialogue: 0,0:14:21.74,0:14:24.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,that all ring at the same time every day at 11:00 AM?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:24.98,0:14:31.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I dunno. Maybe it's just one of your grandfather's pranks?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:31.62,0:14:33.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But isn't it strange?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:33.62,0:14:38.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'd use all the clocks in the house if I were going to pull a prank,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:38.22,0:14:41.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,but it looks like only the digital clocks rang.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:41.26,0:14:42.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Only the digital clocks?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:42.66,0:14:43.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:43.59,0:14:50.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I checked. That cuckoo clock and this alarm clock were set to "off."
Dialogue: 0,0:14:50.84,0:14:55.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He's right! All the analog clocks are set to "off"!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:55.84,0:14:58.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Sure you guys didn't turn them off?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:58.14,0:15:03.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No! We decided not to touch anything\Nuntil this mystery is solved!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:03.85,0:15:07.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It wasn't just the clocks.\NThis VCR was running, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:07.79,0:15:08.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,VCR?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:08.92,0:15:10.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:10.62,0:15:12.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Now I see!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:12.06,0:15:17.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Monjiro{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} must've had a TV show he watched every day at 11:00!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:17.66,0:15:20.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's why he set the alarms!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:20.43,0:15:22.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But don't you think he set too many alarms?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:22.80,0:15:25.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The old guy didn't wake easily.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:25.87,0:15:30.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Anyways, one look at the video and it'll all be clear!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:30.07,0:15:31.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"Play"
Dialogue: 0,0:15:35.18,0:15:38.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This TV isn't connected to an antenna!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:38.88,0:15:40.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It would seem not.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:40.69,0:15:45.76,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Why would you need to wake up\Nif you had the recorder on a timer?!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:45.76,0:15:49.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So why is this video on a timer?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:49.56,0:15:51.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:51.60,0:15:54.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Look here, at the numbers!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:54.17,0:15:57.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There's a weird crack after the zero!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:58.84,0:16:01.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This digital clock has a crack, too!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:01.84,0:16:04.28,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,See! In the same spot!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:04.28,0:16:06.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, so does this one...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:06.71,0:16:08.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A-And this one...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:08.75,0:16:09.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Come to think of it,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:09.85,0:16:15.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,that digital clock in the living room had a similar crack.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:17.22,0:16:19.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What is it, then?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:19.66,0:16:26.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Don't tell me this "110" was left behind by Monjiro{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} as...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:26.93,0:16:28.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,...a code.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:28.63,0:16:30.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What?!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:30.57,0:16:31.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Maybe!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:31.97,0:16:38.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If 110 is a code, it'd make sense that only the digital clocks rang.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:38.24,0:16:42.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,On an analog clock, 11:00 would just be 11 o'clock.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:42.81,0:16:46.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But what could 110 be?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:46.75,0:16:50.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,110 is the emergency police number...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:50.12,0:16:52.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And when you think of the police...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:54.59,0:16:56.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:57.46,0:16:59.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's it!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:00.23,0:17:01.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Dogs!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:01.87,0:17:04.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The police have police dogs!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:04.60,0:17:13.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This "110" means we have to find all the dogs in this house!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:13.18,0:17:18.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Alright! Let's split up and gather every dog in the living room!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:18.92,0:17:23.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,One of the dogs {\i1}has{\i0} to be hiding something!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:25.76,0:17:32.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Collie, German Shepherd, Siberian Husky, Tosa, Doberman...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:32.33,0:17:37.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Dobermans are police dogs, but there's nothing here.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:37.10,0:17:39.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Maybe it's the Dalmatian?!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:39.10,0:17:41.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Remember the movie about those dogs?!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:41.67,0:17:44.81,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}That was "101."
Dialogue: 0,0:17:44.81,0:17:48.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There might still be some other dogs. Keep looking.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:48.78,0:17:50.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Okay!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:55.19,0:17:58.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Dog, dog, dog...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:00.96,0:18:03.12,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}The attic...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:11.14,0:18:13.23,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}It's locked!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:26.18,0:18:30.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Now, now! There's nothing in that room!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:30.39,0:18:35.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And these stairs are dangerous!\NThere's no handrail!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:35.46,0:18:38.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Now come downstairs with me!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:38.13,0:18:40.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,B-B-But there was someone in there!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:40.46,0:18:42.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's the cat!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:42.40,0:18:47.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm sure the kitty would be sad if you hurt yourself.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:47.30,0:18:49.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:49.47,0:18:54.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Conan{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}. What do you say we check the study again?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:54.18,0:18:55.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,'Kay...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:58.08,0:19:04.96,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}No, those were human eyes!\NWhy is he trying to hide it?!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:04.96,0:19:06.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Conan{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:12.43,0:19:16.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Conan{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}. Anything with a dog design. Got it?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:16.77,0:19:18.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:18.20,0:19:21.54,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}It's strange. It's too strange!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:21.54,0:19:24.98,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}There's gotta be something to this mansion!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:27.61,0:19:30.14,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}"File 'Goblin'"...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:31.38,0:19:33.95,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}You mean them?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:32.71,0:19:39.16,Signs,,0,0,0,,Bandits of the Wind!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:33.95,0:19:39.16,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}It is! These are articles about the Goblins, the Bandits of the Wind!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:39.16,0:19:43.29,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}But why are these articles filed here?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:43.29,0:19:49.43,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}The Goblins targeted corrupt businessmen's safes and illicit deals!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:49.43,0:19:54.17,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Because they were so swift, they were called the Bandits of the Wind
Dialogue: 0,0:19:54.17,0:19:59.48,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}and they always left creepy goblin figures wherever they struck.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:59.48,0:20:04.01,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}The name "Goblin" refers to the malicious European spirits
Dialogue: 0,0:20:04.01,0:20:07.75,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}and familiars that would take up residence in homes.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:07.75,0:20:10.58,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}They possess a bizarre form.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:14.42,0:20:19.38,Signs,,0,0,0,,They've Stopped!? Mystery of the Goblins
Dialogue: 0,0:20:15.49,0:20:21.00,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}It's been ten years since the Goblins ceased their activities.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:21.00,0:20:23.73,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Oh, so no one's been caught yet?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:25.14,0:20:30.71,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}"Estimated to Have Eight Members! Leader Named 'Demon'"...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:30.71,0:20:32.20,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Demon?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:33.48,0:20:36.71,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}That was the name on the golf bag...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:36.71,0:20:39.38,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Could it be?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:39.38,0:20:41.99,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}A mirror?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:41.99,0:20:47.12,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Huh? It's attached to the desk! Why?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:49.53,0:20:53.56,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Say, there was a hole in the wall behind me...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:53.56,0:20:57.40,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}And right above it is the cuckoo clock.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:57.40,0:20:58.84,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}The hole in the wall.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:58.84,0:21:01.71,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}The immobile mirror facing the hole.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:01.71,0:21:05.20,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}And the cuckoo clock opposite it and above the hole...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:15.19,0:21:16.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ran!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:16.62,0:21:20.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ran! I'm coming!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:22.66,0:21:24.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What is it, Ran?!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:24.60,0:21:26.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,T-There!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:37.68,0:21:40.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Demon figures...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:40.84,0:21:46.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Demons aren't animals! What are such creepy things doing there?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:46.75,0:21:51.42,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Those aren't just demons. They're goblins!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:51.42,0:21:57.12,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}They're definitely what the Bandits of the Wind used to leave behind!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:58.43,0:22:01.13,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}But why three of them?!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:01.13,0:22:07.54,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Just what kind of mystery are these three goblins hiding?!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:45.00,0:23:48.27,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey! Don't tell me those figures are...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:49.81,0:23:51.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What did you say?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:51.08,0:23:52.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, nothing!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:53.81,0:23:55.98,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Ah.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:55.98,0:24:00.28,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Now I see what's going on here!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:04.92,0:24:06.91,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}So that's it!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:07.94,0:24:13.95,Signs,,0,0,0,,Next Conan:
Dialogue: 0,0:24:13.95,0:24:18.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Next Conan's Hint: Door
Dialogue: 0,0:24:19.20,0:24:20.95,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,Next time, I solve the mansion's mystery!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:19.20,0:24:20.95,Signs,,0,0,0,,yōkan
Dialogue: 0,0:24:20.95,0:24:22.95,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,It's actually azuki bean jelly.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:20.95,0:24:22.95,Signs,,0,0,0,,yōkan
Dialogue: 0,0:24:22.95,0:24:23.96,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,Huh?
